16:50.092 --> 16:51.093
They stick together.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.848
It was so cool

16:52.470 --> 16:54.848
when that guy

16:52.470 --> 16:54.848
at the truck stop

16:54.889 --> 16:57.057
blew the smoke ring

16:54.889 --> 16:57.057
out of the hole in his throat.

16:57.099 --> 16:58.726
That was fun, wasn't it?

16:58.768 --> 17:01.855
How come you're the only good

16:58.768 --> 17:01.855
one in the family?

17:01.896 --> 17:02.856
Why didn't any of it

17:02.897 --> 17:04.858
rub off on Reese or Malcolm?

17:04.899 --> 17:06.233
Dewey, would you cut it out?

17:06.275 --> 17:08.110
No, I mean it.

17:06.275 --> 17:08.110
You're such a good brother.

17:08.152 --> 17:10.070
I'll bet they didn't

17:08.152 --> 17:10.070
even appreciate it.

17:10.112 --> 17:12.907
Dewey! I was never like this

17:10.112 --> 17:12.907
with Reese and Malcolm.

17:12.949 --> 17:14.074
I treated them like crap.

17:14.116 --> 17:15.702
Way worse than

17:14.116 --> 17:15.702
they treat you.

17:15.743 --> 17:17.495
That's impossible.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.288
I tortured them all the time.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.288
I beat them up,

17:19.330 --> 17:20.665
I took their stuff,

17:20.707 --> 17:21.916
I locked them in closets.

17:21.958 --> 17:23.543
You know that scar

17:21.958 --> 17:23.543
on Reese's back?

17:23.584 --> 17:24.752
That's from a bayonet.

17:25.795 --> 17:27.463
Where did I even get a bayonet?!

17:27.505 --> 17:28.965
But you couldn't have.

17:29.007 --> 17:32.259
The way they talk about you...

17:29.007 --> 17:32.259
They love you so much.

17:32.301 --> 17:34.261
Dewey, let me let you in

17:32.301 --> 17:34.261
on a little secret.

17:34.303 --> 17:37.056
Sometimes people love people

17:34.303 --> 17:37.056
for no reason.

17:38.016 --> 17:39.475
Like Whoopi Goldberg.

17:39.517 --> 17:40.727
Hmm.

17:40.768 --> 17:42.520
It's even weirder with brothers.

17:43.980 --> 17:45.773
So you're saying...

17:45.815 --> 17:49.527
I'm the only one

17:45.815 --> 17:49.527
you were ever nice to?

17:49.569 --> 17:50.611
Pretty much.

17:51.821 --> 17:54.365
You know, you have

17:51.821 --> 17:54.365
a real opportunity here.

17:54.407 --> 17:55.700
You can break the cycle.

17:55.742 --> 17:57.326
You can be a good

17:55.742 --> 17:57.326
brother to Jamie.

17:57.368 --> 17:59.161
You can be the one

17:57.368 --> 17:59.161
kid in this family

17:59.203 --> 18:02.081
who takes care of the younger

17:59.203 --> 18:02.081
one and looks out for him.

18:03.165 --> 18:06.126
How is that fair?

18:06.168 --> 18:07.378
Yeah, you're right.

18:08.629 --> 18:09.964
MALCOLM:

18:08.629 --> 18:09.964
Trying to impress

18:10.006 --> 18:11.507
the cool kids?

18:11.549 --> 18:12.717
Hey, Malcolm. Good news.

18:12.759 --> 18:14.719
The head

18:12.759 --> 18:14.719
of security told me

18:14.761 --> 18:16.721
that the surveillance

18:14.761 --> 18:16.721
cameras proved

18:16.763 --> 18:19.139
you didn't flatten

18:16.763 --> 18:19.139
